net.padlocksoftware.padlock.license
Class LicenseTest

java.lang.Object
  net.padlocksoftware.padlock.license.LicenseTest

public final class LicenseTest
extends java.lang.Object

A LicenseTest instance is the fundamental result unit of the Padlock validation process. Each phase of the validation process can be summarized with a LicenseTest instance. As the Validator progresses, instances of LicenseTest are created and added to a TestResult instance.

Padlock has a number of predefined LicenseTest types, which are all defined as public static members of this class. This is done for the convenience of Padlock customers who may want to look through validation results for more details. Instances are compared for equality based strictly on the 'id' field of the LicenseTest object. The following code sample shows how to check a failed validation attempt for the results of the Padlock Hardware test: 

    // Assume a ready validation instance
    LicenseState state = null;
    try {
       state = validator.validate();
       logger.info("All tests passed, enable full functionality.");
    } catch (ValidatorException e) {
       state = ex.getLicenseState();
       if (state.getFailedTests().contains(LicenseTest.HARDWARE)) {
          logger.info("Hardware test failed, just thought you should know.");
       }
    }
Padlock only utilizes the static, immutable LicenseTest instances shown in the 'Field Summary' below. This makes for easy comparisons and inquiries into the results of Padlock's built in tests.

Developers who are creating their own ValidatorPlugin classes need to simply create instances of this class with the appropriate constructor parameters.

Author:
Jason Nichols (jason@padlocksoftware.net)

Field Detail

SIGNED

public static final LicenseTest SIGNED
The Padlock test checking that the license is signed. A passing result for this test indicates the license has a signature, but makes no attempt to verify the signature with a public key.

SIGNATURE

public static final LicenseTest SIGNATURE
The Padlock test checking for a valid license signature. A passing result for this test indicates that the license has a verifiable signature with the corresponding public/private keypair used in the validation process. When passing, this license is guaranteed to be both authentic (created by the private key owner) and unmodified. This is one of the most important tests performed by Padlock. Only when this test passes can you be assured the data contained within the license hasn't been tampered with.

PRIOR

public static final LicenseTest PRIOR
The Padlock test ensuring that the current system date is after the license start date. A passing result ensures that the license validity start period has occured.

EXPIRED

public static final LicenseTest EXPIRED
The Padlock test ensuring that the current system date (as reported by the OS or determined heuristically by Padlock) is before the license expiration date, if it exists. A passing result ensures that the end of the liense validity period has not yet been reached.

BLACKLIST

public static final LicenseTest BLACKLIST
The Padlock test ensuring that the license in question is not blacklisted. A passing result means the license signature does not match any of the signatures on the blacklist passed to the validator.

HARDWARE

public static final LicenseTest HARDWARE
The Padlock test ensuring that the license in question is valid for the hardware running the validation. If the license contains hardware addresses, one of the listed addresses must match at least one of the hardware addresses on the local system.
